From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Stage0 package registration for mismatched bootstrap versions

When using a newer bootstrap GHC (e.g., 9.6.7 to build 9.2.8), the
bootstrap may have different package versions than the source. For
example, bootstrap has template-haskell-2.20.0.0 while source has
template-haskell-2.18.0.0.

The original logic checks if a package NAME is in stagePackages to
decide between copyConf (copy from bootstrap) and buildConf (build
from source). But when the VERSION differs, we need to copy from
bootstrap, not build from source.

This patch compares the requested conf file's package-id with what
the source package would produce. If they differ, use copyConf.

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
@@ -101,14 +101,22 @@
     -- Register a package.
     root -/- relativePackageDbPath stage -/- "*.conf" %> \conf -> do
         historyDisable

         pkgName <- getPackageNameFromConfFile conf
         let pkg = unsafeFindPackageByName pkgName

         when (pkg == compiler) $ need =<< ghcLibDeps stage

-        isBoot <- (pkg `notElem`) <$> stagePackages Stage0
+        -- Check if this is a boot package (not in source) OR if the
+        -- requested version differs from the source package version.
+        -- This handles the case where bootstrap GHC has different
+        -- package versions than the source being built.
+        notInSource <- (pkg `notElem`) <$> stagePackages Stage0
+        srcPkgId <- pkgIdentifier pkg
+        let confPkgId = takeBaseName conf
+            versionMismatch = confPkgId /= srcPkgId
+            isBoot = notInSource || versionMismatch

         let ctx = Context stage pkg vanilla
         case stage of
             Stage0 | isBoot -> copyConf  rs ctx conf
             _               -> buildConf rs ctx conf
